 Port Elizabeth - A brave shop owner from Walmer, in Port Elizabeth, and his assistant fought with and apprehended a suspect, who had allegedly pointed a firearm at him and demanded money on Friday. "It is alleged that at about 09:50, a 30-year-old male was behind the counter of his shop at the corners of Westly and Africa Streets in Walmer location when an unknown man walked in and took dish washing liquid and a bottle of oil off the shelf," described police spokesperson, Col Priscilla Naidu. "As the complainant was placing the items into a bag, the man pulled out a firearm and pointed it at him. "The complainant was instructed to open the gate behind the counter and come out." She said that the complainant called out to his assistant, who was at the back of the shop. "The suspect demanded money and when he was denied any cash, he assaulted the assistant on the head with the firearm. "The complainant and the witness then attacked the suspect and managed to overpower him.," Col Naidu said. "The firearm was kicked under a bed. "The complainant managed to pin down the suspect while his assistant went for help." She said that the 20-year-old suspect was arrested and detained on a charge of attempted business robbery. "The pistol was not reported stolen – it belonged to a deceased person from Mthatha. The suspect will appear in the Port Elizabeth Magistrate's Court on Monday." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 